						<div class="postbody">Disch I think you may have made the light come on. So that I am sure I understand, let's try one last example. (I learn by others correcting)
<br />
<br />duty cycle type of 4 (-_----)
<br />$4002 = $D0
<br />$4003 = $07 (only the low 3 bits are are used) 
<br />
<br />period = ($7D0 + 1) * 2 = 4002 (roughly 4000 so....)
<br />which is a wave at 1.79MHz / 4002 = 445 or roughly a middle C?
<br /> <div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />CPU in thousnads of cycles : _________ 01234567890123456789012345<br />Duty Cycle Timer : ___________________ 0&nbsp; 1&nbsp; 2&nbsp; 3&nbsp; 4&nbsp; 5&nbsp; 6&nbsp; 7&nbsp; <br />output : _____________________________ HHHLLLLLLHHHHHHHHHHHHHHH<br /></div></div>

